All Classes

Class Description
Buffer<T>
Class Buffer uses a LinkedList of generic objects T to create a synchronized buffer to ensure that separate threads handle the information sequentially.
ExercisesController
Controller ExercisesController handles the Exercises scene where the user can select which quiz they want to enter, the method is an action event from userinput, this controller extends MainMenuControllerParent
HomeController
Controller for handling button-presses in the scene Home.fxml.
LogInController
Controller for handling button-presses in the scene LogIn.fxml.
Main
Main is responsible for starting the application, and instantly hands over control of the Stage to MainController.
MainController
Class MainController is controller of the other controllers.
MainMenuControllerParent
An abstract class that extends the SceneController, as this too will be used by scene controllers.
NationalTestController  
NetworkController
Class Network handles the outgoing and incoming information to and from the server.
NewUserController
Controller for handling button-presses in the scene NewUser.fxml.
Person  
Questions
The Questions class will store all the questions
QuizCompletedController
Class QuizCompletedController that extends SceneControllerParent that handles the fxml file QuizCompleted.fxml and shows the user their final score from the quiz
QuizController
Class QuizController that extends SceneControllerParent that handles the fxml file Quiz.fxml and creates actions in the Scene
SceneControllerParent
An interface that all scene-controllers will implement, so that they can easily communicate with the MainController
ScenesEnum
Enum for all the available scenes.
ScenesHashMap
Class ScenesHashMap creates a HashMap of pairs for easy access to scene.
SettingsController  
User
The user class that is responsible for each new user
